# Screens & navigation

## Screens
- Screens live in **`src/screens/`**. Each file exports a default screen component.
- Import **api** (habitService, completionService, supabase), **utils** (COLORS, FONTS), and **components** from `src/`:

```javascript
// ✅ Inside src/screens/HomeScreen.js
import { DateHeader, WeekOverview, HabitItem } from '../components';
import { COLORS, FONTS } from '../utils';
import { getHabits, getCompletionsForDateRange } from '../api';
```

- Use **useFocusEffect** when screen must refetch data on tab/focus. Handle loading and errors in UI.

## Navigation
- **Root navigator** in `src/navigation/RootNavigator.js`. Import screens from `../screens` (or `src/screens`).
- **Bottom tabs** in `src/components/organisms/BottomTabNavigator.js`; import screens from `../../screens`.
- Keep route names and params consistent (e.g. `HabitDetail` with `habit` param).

## App entry
- **App.js** imports `RootNavigator` from `./src/navigation` and `supabase` from `./src/api`. New app-level code should use `src/` imports.
